#                                                                                                            #
#  you can get more information about CS-Rosetta from http://spin.niddk.nih.gov/bax/software/CSROSETTA/  	 	 #
#                                                                                                            #
##############################################################################################################

Programs needed to be downloaded and installed:
	1. NMRPipe
			 http://spin.niddk.nih.gov/NMRPipe/

	2. TALOS+
			 http://spin.niddk.nih.gov/NMRPipe/talos/

	3. CS-Rosetta package from Ad Bax's group
			 http://spin.niddk.nih.gov/bax/software/CSROSETTA/

	4. Download chemical shifts data from "bmrb" - should be better have at lease 3 data type(1H, 13C, 15N).
		 If you are under unix-based system, with the access number 15112 you can simply do:
		 $ wget http://rest.bmrb.wisc.edu/bmrb/NMR-STAR2/15112
		 $ mv 15112 15112.bmrb

	5. to change the bmrb format into talos format:
		 $ ./bmrb2talos.com 15112.bmrb > 15112.talos

Then you just run this command:
	$ ./cmd									// run cmd

	-> files you need:
	1. 15112.talos						// input chemical shifts file with talos format
	2. nmrInit.linux9.com			// env setup for NMRPipe, remember to edit the paths 
	3. talos+Init.com					// env setup for TALOS+, remember to edit the paths
	4. run_talos							// tcsh script to run TALOS+, modify input file 

	-> outputs that are going to be used for fragments picking at STEP3	
	1. pred.ss.tab						// secondary structure prediction
	2. pred.tab								// phi/psi angel prediction 
